library(RColorBrewer)
library(cowplot)
library(colorRamps)
library(ggrepel)
## Loading required package: ggplot2
library(ggspatial)
library(sf)
## Linking to GEOS 3.13.0, GDAL 3.8.5, PROJ 9.5.1; sf_use_s2() is TRUE
library(dplyr)  
## 
## Attaching package: 'dplyr'
## The following objects are masked from 'package:stats':
## 
##     filter, lag
## The following objects are masked from 'package:base':
## 
##     intersect, setdiff, setequal, union
setwd("/Volumes/Elements SE/Figure1-maps")
group <- read.csv("group.csv",sep=",",header=T,row.names = 1) #  group 
unique_locations <- group %>%
    group_by(Location) %>%
    summarise(
        Latitude = first(Latitude),
        Longitude = first(Longitude)
    )

# 
print(unique_locations)
## # A tibble: 3  3
##   Location Latitude Longitude
##   <chr>       <dbl>     <dbl>
## 1 Erguna       50.1      119.
## 2 Xilinhot     43.4      116.
## 3 Yucheng      36.6      116.
unique_locations<-as.data.frame(unique_locations)
group<-unique_locations[,c(2,3)]
rownames(group)<-unique_locations$Location

#  `group`  sf 
site.CFB2 <- st_as_sf(group, coords = c("Longitude", "Latitude"), crs = 4326)
site.CFB2$sample_name<-row.names(group)

#  sample_name 
site.CFB2$Site <- factor(site.CFB2$sample_name, levels = c("Erguna" ,  "Xilinhot", "Yucheng" ))

china <- st_read("China.json")
## Reading layer `china' from data source 
##   `/Volumes/Elements SE/Figure1-maps/china.json' using driver `GeoJSON'
## Simple feature collection with 35 features and 10 fields
## Geometry type: MULTIPOLYGON
## Dimension:     XY
## Bounding box:  xmin: 73.50235 ymin: 3.397162 xmax: 135.0957 ymax: 53.56327
## Geodetic CRS:  WGS 84
colors <- colorRampPalette(c("red", "#FFD700", "blue"))(3)  # 27

mapCN<-ggplot() + 
    geom_sf(data = china,fill="NA",color="grey",size=0.5) + 
    #geom_sf(data = nine_line,color="black",size=0.5) + 
    scale_size(range = c(1,5))+
    annotation_scale(location = "bl") +
    annotation_north_arrow(location = "tl", which_north = "true",
                           style = north_arrow_fancy_orienteering)+
    geom_sf(data=site.CFB2,aes(color=Site),size=5)+
    geom_text_repel(data = site.CFB2,aes(label=sample_name,geometry=geometry),stat = "sf_coordinates",color="blue",size=5)+
    #annotate("text",x=-2556175.2,y=-2387082,label="GS(2022)1061",size=3)+
    scale_colour_manual(values= colors,name="Site latitude")+
    coord_sf(ylim = c(-2387082,1654989),xlim = c(-2556175.2,2816095),crs = "+proj=laea +lat_0=40 +lon_0=104")+
    theme_bw()+xlab("Longitude")+ylab("Latitude")+
    theme(plot.margin=unit(c(0,0,0,0),"mm"),
          axis.text = element_text(size = 18,colour = "black",face = "bold"),
          axis.title = element_text(size = 18,colour = "black",face = "bold"))

mapCN_nineline<-ggplot() + 
  geom_sf(data = china,fill="NA",color="grey",size=0.5) +
  scale_size(range = c(1,5))+
  annotation_scale(location = "br") +
  coord_sf(ylim = c(-4228017,-1877844),xlim = c(117131.4,2115095),crs="+proj=laea +lat_0=40 +lon_0=104")+
  theme_bw()+theme(aspect.ratio = 1.5,plot.margin=unit(c(0,0,0,0),"mm"))

ggdraw()+
    draw_plot(mapCN)+
  draw_plot(mapCN_nineline,x = 0.715, y = 0.095, width = 0.25, height = 0.230)

ggsave("SampleSiteMap.pdf", width = 12, height = 8.5)
